result.name: Bread & Bistro

reviews.text:
Service varied among the different servers.  
Food qualify was quite poor.
We had pancakes, beef patty with rice in curry sauce (yes, “in” a generous pool of sauce) and cheese burger.
The beef in the rice and burger tasted a remote hint of beef, and they charge $138 for the burger! 
In the curry rice, there was a hard crusted ring shaped thing where they put the egg in, so hard that it wouldn’t give in to a bite even after soaking in the curry sauce for a good 15 minutes...  We asked the server what that was supposed to be, and were told that it’s an onion ring.  They did have the courtesy to offer replacement of the onion haha.

I’m not incredibly impressed with this place. How on earth can pancakes take 30 minutes to prepare? I ordered the eggs Benedict instead; eggs were barely cooked and the hollandaise was tasteless.  It was very nice that they have baby high chairs at least, but the service was lacklustre.
Unpleasant service and pastries served frozen or they insist to warm it up in their microwave because it’s not fresh...just disgusting

They must have taken the recent poor ratings quite seriously as the service was not poor at all, and the quality of the food is decent. Might have helped that we visited at 11am on a Sat which meant there were few customers. We were seated immediately and water served, table set, menu provided and explained efficiently. Place is spacious and comfortable but it is not cheap. Had the $98 souffle pancakes (20 min needed, told to us in advance. delicious, more like a dessert), and the avocado crab salad ($138 - tasty but unnecessarily expensive, could do without the crab and truffle dressing to lower the price imo).
The worst. If your souffle pancake is not available everyday, put it in your poster or something. Very disappointed.
